            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Location 2:</emph>
                Located in the PDC, power distribution center, under the hood
            </para>
            <figure id="f7300020b" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G7300088.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>On most vehicles, there are unused ignition bussed fuse locations in the PDC. These can be used for
                low current ignition loads provided that the total ignition load in the PDC does not exceed the 40A
                rating for the ISO cube ignition relay. For Relay and Fuse descriptions, see the product graphic located
                on the inside of the PDC cover.
            </para>
            <para>To add circuits to the Maxi Fuse Block, the block must first be removed. The Maxi fuse block is held
                in with three snaps. In some cases, the Micro Fuse block, Micro Relay Blocks and the Mini Relay blocks
                will have to be removed.
            </para>
            <para>To remove the other blocks, remove sliding harness entrance door, spread out side of PDC to unlatch
                Micro Fuse and Relay blocks. Slide out Mini Relay blocks Note, if blocks are too tight, using a 3/16
                square bar insert into square hole in bottom of PDC and tap blocks loose.
            </para>
            <para>Fuse terminal part numbers</para>
            <para>18 gauge - 3515517c1</para>
            <para>16 gauge - 3573312c1</para>
            <para>14 gauge - 3516158c1</para>
            <para>12 gauge - 3516158c1</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>For Battery taps, test to see that battery voltage is present at all times.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>For Accessory taps, test to see that battery voltage is present when the ignition key is in
                        "Accessory" or "Ignition" key states
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>For Ignition taps, test to see that battery voltage is present when the ignition key is in
                        "Ignition" key state.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
